# Service hub: {{ .Service }}

This directory is a **devbox service workspace** for the `{{ .Service }}` service of project `{{ .Project.Name }}`. It is a generated hub — not the application repository itself.

The application code lives in `src/`. If the project ships its own `AGENTS.md` or `CLAUDE.md` inside `src/`, treat that as authoritative for code-level conventions (framework, structure, tests, lint). It may also be absent — in that case orient yourself from whatever the project provides (`README.md`, the package manifest, the test layout, etc.).

## Workspace layout

- `src/` — the application repository (project source; may have its own `AGENTS.md` / `CLAUDE.md`)
- `configs/` — service config files mounted into the container
- `logs/` — service runtime logs
- `home/` — container user `$HOME` (shell history, tool caches)
- `runtime/` — ephemeral runtime state (sockets, pids, scratch)
- `.devcontainer/` — Dev Containers config (generated)
- `.vscode/` — VS Code workspace settings (generated)
- `AGENTS.md` / `CLAUDE.md` — this file (generated; `CLAUDE.md` is a symlink to `AGENTS.md`)

Everything outside `src/` is owned by devbox: regenerated on `devbox render` / deploy, gitignored at the project root, and safe to recreate. Do not edit this file by hand — it is rendered from `devbox/templates/ai/`.

